OL,3,COffer from council over Birmingham bin
OL,4,Cdispute 'watered down', says Unite
OL,6,FThe union also said the offer was made
OL,7,Fby government commissioners and the
OL,8,Fleader of the council, Councillor John
OL,9,FCotton, who were not in the
OL,10,Fnegotiating room.
OL,12,FMembers of Unite have been on all-out
OL,13,Fstrike in a row over pay and jobs,
OL,14,Fleading to bags of refuse piling up
OL,15,Facross the city.
OL,17,FOn Thursday (29 May), an injunction
OL,18,Fbrought by to stop striking bin
OL,19,Fworkers from obstructing bin lorries
OL,20,Fwas extended indefinitely.
